>Description:
It would be nice to have a bitmap/file function in the 2htdp/image teachpack, since 'bitmap' is a macro, it's not helpful for loading from a file whose name is computed and stored in a variable at runtime. It's possible to use bitmap/url with a file:// url, but that doesn't seem to be able to do relative paths.
>How-To-Repeat:

>Fix:
>Audit-Trail:
From: Robby Findler <robby@eecs.northwestern.edu>
To: nadeem@acm.org, bugs@racket-lang.org
Cc: nobody@racket-lang.org, bug-notification@racket-lang.org
Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/12466: Request a bitmap/file function in 2htdp/image
Date: Wed, 28 Dec 2011 21:27:06 -0600

 Bitmaps computed at runtime will not work well with executable
 creation, which is why I've resisted using that before.
 
 Any thoughts about that?
 
 Robby
 
