From: Nadeem Abdul Hamid <nadeem@acm.org>
To: Robby Findler <robby@eecs.northwestern.edu>
Cc: bugs@racket-lang.org, nobody@racket-lang.org,
        bug-notification@racket-lang.org
Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/12466: Request a bitmap/file function in 2htdp/image
Date: Thu, 29 Dec 2011 09:10:45 -0500

 Well, the same problem exists with the functions of the batch-io
 library. But it just means that the external resources (data
 files/image files) have to manually (or some other way) be put in the
 expected location in order to be found (if by "not work well" you mean
 that the external resources don't get included in the distribution
 archive) -- as long as the files are in the expected location with
 respect to the executable, they seem to get loaded fine when run.
 
 
